The anonymity of abortion contributes to the women feeling separated from the abortion regulation authorities. Something needs to be done to make women take responsibility for their actions.
Today we do know that illegal abortion is the reason for many women to fall victim to fatal illnesses, which could have probably been avoided by having abortion performed under qualified medical supervision and care. It would be shameful for medical specialists not to contribute to the wellbeing of their patients and society.
There are alternatives to abortion:
 Contraception (birth control pills, IUD, condom etc.) before pregnancy would avoid abortion;  If there is an unwanted pregnancy, it is possible to maintain it and take care of the child, which would also avoid the need for important resources allocated to abortion.
 Maternity leave (in case woman has maternity leave allowance) is a social right of working women. This means that she can take care of the baby and the state will pay her maternity leave allowance, based on the size of the family allowances.
There is no maternal leave in Estonia because the lack of it limits labor market participation of women, and the positive effects of the legislation adopting child birth leave compensating for the lack of maternity leave is uncertain.
I strongly support the legislative changes if the state starts granting pregnant, childbirth-bound and child-rearing bound mothers with child allowances and maternity benefits, together with the change of the term maternity leave to child birth
